==Korean==
===Etymology===
From Chinese [[人]], human + [[形]], form
===Noun===
'''인형''' (人形, inhyeong)
# [[doll]] {{f}} or [[action figure]] {{m}}; puppet; little human form
===Usage note===
Korean-American girls translate their 인형 toys as [[doll]] while Korean-American boys translate theirs as "[[action figure]]". When I told some 12-year-olds that they were "playing with dolls" they took offense - mightily! ;-)